From acbc28544e23f76619858a00c39779f0f1763bb7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?=C3=8D=C3=B1igo=20Huguet?= <ihuguet@riseup.net>
Date: Mon, 29 Dec 2025 09:44:51 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Don't set home dir for nm-openvpn user

Fix sysusers.d file to not define any home directory. The user doesn't
need a home directory, the directory defined was not in /home nor used
as home, and the documentation recommends not to define it:
www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/latest/sysusers.d.html
---
 nm-openvpn-sysusers.conf.in | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/nm-openvpn-sysusers.conf.in b/nm-openvpn-sysusers.conf.in
index 8ec9b015..1df97dbe 100644
--- a/nm-openvpn-sysusers.conf.in
+++ b/nm-openvpn-sysusers.conf.in
@@ -1 +1 @@
-u! nm-openvpn - "NetworkManager OpenVPN" @LOCALSTATEDIR@/lib/openvpn/chroot
+u! nm-openvpn - "NetworkManager OpenVPN" - -
-- 
